cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.EM, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the design and characterization of superconducting nanowire-based processors for accelerating deep neural network training. This topic falls under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET) as it involves the use of a novel technology for processing. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of crossbar architectures, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also focuses on the acceleration of deep neural network training, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The electro-thermal circuit simulations mentioned in the paper fall under the category of electromagnetics (cs.EM), and the validation of the concept using an emulator falls under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
